{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W3MJBFjRjBVdYbBDgT88oD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The malformed HTTP response is HTTP/2 being sent on what kubectl proxy expects to be HTTP/1.1. The CockroachDB admin UI uses HTTP/2, but the kubectl proxy is doing plain HTTP/1.1 which breaks on HTTP/2.\n\nLet me try a different approach — use port-forward directly to the pod and then curl with HTTP/2 or TLS-skipping.\n\nActually, let me try `kubectl port-forward` properly and use curl with `-k` and `--http2`.\n\nWait - actually the malformed response `\\x00\\x00\\x12\\x04` is an HTTP/2 preface frame (SETTINGS frame). \n\nThe CockroachDB HTTP server is speaking HTTP/2 but we're sending HTTP/1.1 requests. Since the readiness probes are working and the pods are healthy, the issue is just that my client tools need to handle HTTP/2 properly — I should try port-forward with curl using `--http2-prior-knowledge`.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1144,"cache_read_input_tokens":46967,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1144},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8015f21e-1368-44bb-afee-00dd3cb21624","uuid":"0392affd-83d9-4ef8-b8af-5acf8c281064","request_id":"req_011CbyGGT6Fo9zSghGPe1VY1"}
