{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015B89bGfHFC2NuxSxk83zoj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is fully recovered. Summary of what happened and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** The StatefulSet command contained a deliberate fault — a shell conditional that bound `crdb-cluster-1`'s HTTP server to `127.0.0.1:8080` (loopback) instead of `0.0.0.0:8080`. This made the Kubernetes readiness probe (`/health?ready=1`) unreachable from outside the pod's loopback interface, so the probe failed and the pod was never marked Ready.\n\n**Fix:** Patched the StatefulSet to remove the conditional and always use `--http-addr=0.0.0.0:8080` for all pods. Then manually deleted `crdb-cluster-1` to break the rolling-update deadlock (the update couldn't proceed because it waits for the pod to become Ready, but the pod needed the update to become Ready).\n\n**Verification:**\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts\n- StatefulSet: `3/3 READY`\n- No Unhealthy events for any pod since the recreation"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1539,"cache_read_input_tokens":49233,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1539},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8015f21e-1368-44bb-afee-00dd3cb21624","uuid":"f4b693cb-90a5-4069-9d48-e85b39cbd1fa","request_id":"req_011CbyGKESLSQ3BEm5dfyc8b"}
